citations:
    citation-affc-samwell-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Samwell I"
            text_from_source: "You have no father. Only brothers. Only us. Your life belongs to the Night's Watch, so go and stuff your smallclothes into a sack, along with anything else you care to take to Oldtown."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Samwell Tarly. Set at Castle Black in the early days of Jon Snow's Lord Commandership. Sam has been researching the Others in the Night's Watch archives. Jon orders Sam to take Maester Aemon and Gilly (and her babe) south by sea to Braavos, then on to Oldtown, so Sam can forge a maester's chain. Aemon is at risk because Melisandre covets his Targaryen blood for king's-blood sacrifices. Sam reports his research on the Others: dragonglass kills them, fire dismays them, dragonsteel (Valyrian steel) may also harm them. Key figures: Pyp, Grenn, Dolorous Edd Tollett, Black Jack Bulwer, Hairy Hal, Mully, Three-Finger Hobb, Kedge Whiteye, Left Hand Lew, Ulmer, Clydas (Maester Aemon's steward), Dareon (a singer assigned to accompany them to Eastwatch). Sam drops and muddles the book 'Maester Thomax's Dragonkin' and Colloquo Votar's 'Jade Compendium.' Aemon leaves the Jade Compendium for Jon with a passage marked. Establishes the ship Blackbird will carry them from Eastwatch to Braavos."
